cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the ability of neural models to capture lexicosyntactic inferences in the context of event factuality prediction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the behavior of current state-of-the-art neural systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with natural language processing and inference. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper focuses on neural models. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the performance of neural models in a specific task (event factuality prediction) and may use techniques commonly used in computer vision and pattern recognition.
